http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/KSRTC-police-to-conduct-separate-investigations/article14025924.ece

The KSRTC and police officials said they would conduct separate investigations to ascertain the cause of the accident. Many possibilities, including flat tyres, mechanical problem in the steering rod, attempting to overtake another bus, and carelessness of the driver, are being examined.Experts at the department will inspect the condition of the tyres, steering rod, brakes, axels and other parts, he said.According to the police and KSRTC officials, the vehicle was being driven at a speed of less than 50 kmph, when it met with the accident.